The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 22 November is 8,494 (983.1 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 17 November, there were 1,057 new confirmed cases (122.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 10 November, there were 966 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 9% ( 91 extra cases).
